Citation.sAbstract: Viscosities and densities of d-glucose.water mixtureswere measured, and conductivities in the NiSO4.dglucose.  water systemwere also measured at 278.15.308.15K in 5K intervals. Based on the Lee.Wheaton  conductivity equation, values of limiting molar conductivities  0 and association constants KA were  obtained. Changes in the standard thermodynamic functions, Gibbs energy  G.  A(T), enthalpy  H.  A(T),  and entropy  S.  A(T), for a process of ion-pair formation were calculated at different temperatures. The  results show that (1) at given temperatures, the  0 values for 1/2NiSO4 decrease with increasing concentrations  of d-glucose; (2) at fixed concentrations of d-glucose, the  0 values for 1/2NiSO4 increase  with increasing temperature; and (3) the process of association of NiSO4 is controlled by the change in  entropy  S.  A.
Citation.sTitle: Conductivity in NiSO4 d-glucose water solutions at 278.15 308.15K
